     "{\"template\":\"intro\",\"texts\":[\"Our Safety and Citizenship team provide a free-of-charge transport education service to schools within London.\"],\"link\":{\"image\":{}},\"image\":{},\"wrapped\":false}",
     "Our aim is to promote safe, responsible and respectful behaviour on and around London's transport system.",
     "We provide a range of services to schools and community groups in London, from \u003ca href=\"/info-for/schools-and-young-people/safety-and-citizenship/primary-pre-transiti\"\u003ein-school presentations\u003c/a\u003e and Junior Citizenship Schemes to community events and \u003ca href=\"/info-for/schools-and-young-people/safety-and-citizenship/restorative-justice\"\u003erestorative justice\u003c/a\u003e .",
     "We offer our\u003cstrong\u003efree\u003c/strong\u003e presentation service to all of London's primary schools and we also visit around 20,000 secondary school pupils a year.",
     "Sessions are delivered by an experienced School Liaison Officer, who may be accompanied by members of local Metropolitan Police Service Safer Transport Teams.",
     "Presentations and resources are designed to support the PSHCE curriculum. We can deliver to audiences of up to 300. Sessions are adapted to ensure the best learning experience for each audience. The lesson plans section supports sessions in class, before and after a visit from our team.",
     "Find out more about our TfL Safety and Citizenship work below.",
     "{\"template\":\"video\",\"style\":\"4m0q58t6aew\",\"link\":{\"image\":{}},\"image\":{},\"wrapped\":false}"
